        "text": "Citation Guide Chicago Notes & Bibliography: Citation Examples + Rules Chicago Notes & Bibliography (18th ed.): Citation Examples & Essential Rules For NPS theses, papers, and publications: to cite properly, follow the citation examples and apply the essential rules. The Chicago Manual of Style leaves a great deal unspecified and up to interpretation. The NPS Citation Guide streamlines and simplifies Chicago's guidance; your professors, GWC instructors, and thesis processors may interpret or explain Chicago's guidelines slightly differently. Ultimately, the responsibility for clear attribution of source material lies with you, the author. Citation ExamplesEssential Rules Artificial Intelligence (GenAI) arXiv Blog Book Audiobook Chapter in Edited Book Electronic Print Class Notes, Lecture, Presentation, Workshop Computer Program / Software Conference Paper / Proceedings Data Set / Database Dictionary / Encyclopedia Author given Organization as author Fact Sheet Government / Military Document Directive Doctrine Field Manual Government Report CRS Report GAO Report Strategy Document / Other Government Report Instruction Memorandum Military Regulation Handbook Journal Article Legal Bill / Resolution Code of Federal Regulations Congressional Hearing Full Hearing Testimony Court Case Decision Executive Order Public Law Magazine Article Map Multimedia Film Podcast Video Newspaper Article Patent Personal Communication Report Research Report / Think Tank Report / White Paper Technical Report Secondary / Indirect Source Social Media Speech Standard Thesis / Dissertation Think Tank Report Unpublished / Informally Published Works Website / Webpage Janes Example White Paper Wikipedia (not recommended) Working Paper / Occasional Paper Accessed Dates Author Names: Honorifics Authors: Identifying Authors of Official Documents Bibliography vs. List of References Capitalization: Title Case vs. Sentence case Country Names with Government Organizations Figures / Images / Graphs Footnote Placement & Signal Phrases How Often to Cite? Ibid. / Shortened Citations Missing Info Multiple Authors, et al. Multiple Citations in a Single Sentence Online Sources: Links Page Numbers and Other Locators Print vs. Online Sources Secondary / Indirect Sources Tables Translations and Works Not in English"
