        "text": "If you do not see an example that matches your source type or the rule that you need, consult the Additional Resources for your style.\n\nCitation Examples Artificial Intelligence (GenAI) While generative AI can help you develop initial understanding of a topic, it should not be cited in your work as a source of reliable information; see Guidance for Gen AI Use in Academic Work and DKL's GenAI research guide. Source TypeGeneric ExampleActual Example N = Footnote S = Shortened Citation B = Bibliography / List of References entry See also Capitalization (Title Case / Sentence case) GenAI If the prompt is included in your text: N: Text generated by Name of Software, Company, full date, URL. or If the prompt is not included in your text: N: Name of Software, response to “Prompt,” Company, full date, URL. S: None; use a full citation each time. B: None In your text: Include the relevant portion of the response. N: Text generated by ChatBLT-1.3, SandwichAI, June 24, 2024, https://www.sandwichai.com/chatblt. or N: ChatBLT-1.3, response to \"Calculate the ratio of mayonnaise to bread as a single (n−1)-dimensional hyperplane using the ham sandwich theorem,\" SandwichAI, June 24, 2024, https://www.sandwichai.com/chatblt. S: None B: None In your text: As part of our methodology, we asked ChatBLT-1.3 to \"Calculate the ratio of mayonnaise to bread as a single (n−1)-dimensional hyperplane using the ham sandwich theorem.\" It responded with \"42.\" No reference entry is needed. Zotero will not be used to cite. arXiv Follow guidance in the Essential Rules for including page numbers. Source TypeGeneric ExampleActual Example N = Footnote S = Shortened Citation B = Bibliography / List of References entry See also Capitalization (Title Case / Sentence case) arXiv Zotero N: Author First and Last Name, “Title of Work in Title Case,” arXiv, year, page[s], DOI or URL."
