            "id": "nps-thesis-ieee-citations-pdf-022",
            "text": "Essential Rules Abbreviations IEEE List of Acronyms and Abbreviations from the IEEE Editorial Style Manual, 2023 Accessed Dates Only include date accessed if the source material has no date. Author Names: Honorifics Do not include honorifics (Dr., Col., Professor, etc.) when citing author names. Including these titles in the body of your document is acceptable.\n\nIdentifying Authors of Official Documents For the National Security Strategy, cite the president as the author. For other official documents, the author is the organization immediately responsible for creating the document. In the example below, the author is the Office of the Chief of Naval Operations and the publisher is the Department of the Navy."
