        "guideTitle": "NPS Thesis INFORMS Citations",
        "text": "Citation Guide INFORMS: Citation Examples + Rules INFORMS (v. 1.7, 2020): Citation Examples & Essential Rules For NPS theses, papers, and publications: to cite properly, follow the citation examples and apply the essential rules. Citation ExamplesEssential Rules Artificial Intelligence (GenAI) arXiv Blog Book Chapter in Edited Book Electronic Print Class Notes / Lecture / Presentation / Workshop Computer Program / Software Conference Paper / Proceedings Data Set / Database Dictionary / Encyclopedia Fact Sheet Government / Military Document Directive Doctrine Field Manual Government Report Instruction Military Regulation Strategy Document Handbook Journal Article Legal Bill / Resolution Code of Federal Regulations Congressional Hearing / Testimony within a Hearing Court Case Decision Executive Order Public Law Magazine / Newspaper Article Patent Personal Communication Report Research Report / Think Tank Report / White Paper Technical Report Standard Secondary / Indirect Source Thesis / Dissertation Think Tank Report Unpublished / Informally Published Works Website / Webpage Janes Example White Paper Wikipedia (not recommended) Working Paper / Occasional Paper Abbreviations Acronyms Accessed Dates Author Names: Honorifics Authors: Identifying Authors of Official Documents Bibliography vs. List of References Capitalization: Title Case vs. Sentence case Country Names with Government Organizations Equations Figures / Images / Graphs How Often to Cite? In-text Citation Placement & Signal Phrases Missing Info Multiple Authors, et al. Multiple Sources in One Citation No Date Given Online Sources: Links Page Numbers Print vs. Online Sources Same Author, Multiple Works Secondary / Indirect Sources Tables"
