        "guideTitle": "NPS Thesis INFORMS Citations",
        "text": "Accessed Dates Always include date accessed for webpages. Acronyms To introduce an acronym in a parenthetical citation, spell out the organization name first, then include the acronym in brackets, as here: First citation: (Chief of Naval Operations [CNO]) Subsequent citations: (CNO) It doesn't matter if you've already defined the acronym in the text; ensure it is spelled out in the parenthetical citation as well. Do not include acronyms for organizations listed as authors in the List of References. Author Names: Honorifics Do not include honorifics (Dr., Col., Professor, etc.) when citing author names. Including these titles in the body of your document is acceptable. Identifying Authors of Official Documents For the National Security Strategy, cite the president as the author. For other official documents, the author is the organization immediately responsible for creating the document. In the example below, the author is the Office of the Chief of Naval Operations and the publisher is the Department of the Navy."
