            "text": "Contentsv Part 2. Editing and Style Introduction to Part 271 Chapter 12. Editing Text73 §12.1. Basic editing74 §12.2. Mathematical symbols in text75 §12.3. Type76 §12.4. Capitalization in lists79 §12.5. Wording80 §12.6. Acronyms83 §12.7. Punctuation84 §12.8. Quotations95 §12.9. Gender-neutral and bias-free language95 §12.10. Miscellaneous applications96 Chapter 13. Editing Mathematics97 §13.1. Numbers97 §13.2. Variables98 §13.3. Standard abbreviated forms of mathematical expressions (inf,max,min, etc.) and functions (sin,cos,tan, etc.)98 §13.4. Punctuation100 §13.5. Line dots (ldots) and centered dots (cdots)102 §13.6. Fences103 §13.7. Sums ( \u0002 ) and products ( \u0003 )104 §13.8. Unions (∪, \u0004 ) and intersections (∩, \u0005 )105 §13.9. Integrals106 §13.10. Fractions107 §13.11. Cases109 §13.12. Matrices110 §13.13. Diagrams111 §13.14. Equation numbers112 §13.15. Spacing in displays113 §13.16. Breaking equations in text114 §13.17. Breaking and aligning equations in displays116"
